Subject: Always emit authorThumbnails field, even when author_thumbnail is nil

SearchVideo#to_json wraps the entire `authorThumbnails` JSON field in
an `if author_thumbnail` guard. When the underlying author_thumbnail is
nil (as it is for entries built by the new LockupViewModelParser added
in PR #5736 — YouTube doesn't include the channel avatar in channel-tab
lockups since you're already on the channel page), the field is omitted
from the response entirely.

Yattee silently filters entries that lack `authorThumbnails`, which
makes the subscription feed and channel pages appear empty even when
the underlying data is correct.

This patch moves the nil guard inside the json.array call so the field
is always present in the response, emitted as `[]` when no thumbnail
is available. Behavior is unchanged when author_thumbnail is non-nil.

---
--- a/src/invidious/helpers/serialized_yt_data.cr
+++ b/src/invidious/helpers/serialized_yt_data.cr
@@ -91,9 +91,9 @@
 
       author_thumbnail = self.author_thumbnail
 
-      if author_thumbnail
-        json.field "authorThumbnails" do
-          json.array do
+      json.field "authorThumbnails" do
+        json.array do
+          if author_thumbnail
             qualities = {32, 48, 76, 100, 176, 512}
 
             qualities.each do |quality|
